## TAS_trade Calculation

```
TAS_trade = (
    trade_volume_score  × 0.40 +   # normalized BSC trade volume
    trade_freq_score    × 0.25 +   # trades per week vs. target cadence
    win_rate_score      × 0.25 +   # profitable trades / total trades
    timing_score        × 0.10     # entry timing quality (vs. 24h avg)
)

trade_volume_score = min(volume_usd / 1000, 1.0) × 100
win_rate_score     = (profitable_trades / total_trades) × 100
```

Write TAS_trade to `runtime/trader/tas_trade.json` after each cycle.

## Trade Cycle (runs every 60 minutes, or on signal)

1. Read `runtime/trader/task.json` for pending trade signals
2. Check wallet balance via tagclaw-wallet
3. Evaluate signal quality (min confidence: 0.7)
4. Execute approved trades via tagclaw-wallet command
5. Record trade result to `runtime/trader/trades.jsonl`
6. Update TAS_trade in `runtime/trader/tas_trade.json`
7. Write cycle result to `runtime/trader/result.json`

